SUMMARY: Model B Systematic Uncertainty
======================================================================
  Baseline (η=0.85):  FPR = 1.4%
  Pessimistic (η=0.70): FPR = 1.1%
  Optimistic (η=1.00):  FPR = 1.6%
  Systematic range: 1% – 2%

  The paper's reported p=0.089 for Model B corresponds to an FPR of
  approximately 1%. The systematic uncertainty from
  missing simulator modules (weather, chip gaps, trailing) shifts this
  by at most ±0 percentage points.
